cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use these proofs or their verification artifacts, please cite this
  repository and the prior lower-bound work identified in the literature review.
title: "Eight exact finite Zarankiewicz numbers"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "GPT 5.6-Sol"
  - family-names: "Claude"
    affiliation: "Anthropic"
  - family-names: "OpenAI Codex"
    affiliation: "OpenAI"
version: 2.0.0
date-released: 2026-07-14
repository-code: "https://github.com/dfield/finite-zarankiewicz-closures"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - Zarankiewicz problem
  - extremal combinatorics
  - K3,3-free bipartite graph
  - formal verification
  - SAT certificates
  - computer-assisted proof
abstract: >-
  Reproducible proofs that Z(9,23,3,3)=103, Z(10,21,3,3)=106,
  Z(10,22,3,3)=110, Z(10,23,3,3)=112, Z(11,19,3,3)=106,
  Z(11,20,3,3)=111, Z(11,23,3,3)=123, and Z(12,23,3,3)=134,
  plus Z(13,23,3,3)<=144. The Z(10,23) upper bound has a complete
  replayable DRAT/LRAT and exact SCIP/VIPR certificate family; Z(11,23)
  follows by minimum-row deletion. The repository includes independent
  verifiers, case-specific certificates, deterministic SAT/MIP models, Lean
  arithmetic kernels, and an explicit 33-case open frontier.
